# Typography

- **Font:** **Arial**, Helvetica, sans-serif everywhere (`src/index.css` `@theme` `--font-sans` and `html`). **Exclude** `.font-mono` where monospace is required (ids, tabular times). No other UI font stacks unless rendering inside a fixed canvas such as a video frame export.
- **Size:** Base size is **14px**, set on `html` in `src/index.css`. Prefer **`text-base`** (1rem) or no size class so copy inherits 14px.
- **Letter-spacing:** **`normal`** globally (`html` in `index.css`). Do not use Tailwind **`tracking-*`** (`tracking-tight`, `tracking-wide`, etc.) on app chrome — it breaks uniformity.

## Allowed exceptions (hierarchy without breaking the system)

- **`text-sm`:** Secondary body — e.g. style kit **character/object description** inputs (one line next to the id).
- **`text-xs`:** **Uppercase section labels** only (e.g. “CHARACTERS”, “OBJECTS” on the style page). Pair with `font-medium uppercase text-muted-foreground`. Do not use `text-xs` for sentence case body text.
- **Ids / codes:** Character kit ids (e.g. `C01`) and **numeric** object ids (three digits, e.g. `010`) in list cards and preview overlay use the app **`font-sans`** stack with **`text-[13px] text-muted-foreground`** beside the name — use **`uppercase`** only for character ids (letter prefix). Preview badge uses **`text-base`**.
- **Ids / codes (inline):** Tabular codes that need alignment may use **`font-mono`** with **`text-base`** (14px).

Do not use arbitrary pixel font sizes (`text-[10px]`, etc.) on app chrome unless there is a documented exception in this file.

- **Style kit / preview** panes that mimic an output video may still use layout-specific sizing if required for aspect ratio; default to `text-base` first.

When editing UI, keep `index.css` aligned: `font-size: 14px`, `font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif`, `letter-spacing: normal`.
